[32m+[m[32m## Unreal WebSocket Protocol (M1.2)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRoomZero exposes an Unreal-focused WebSocket bridge for local-first agent embodiment integration.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Endpoints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- WebSocket connect: `ws://127.0.0.1:8000/ws/unreal/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m[32m- State snapshot (REST): `GET /ws/unreal/state/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Send command to agent (REST): `POST /ws/unreal/command/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Observation list (REST): `GET /ws/unreal/observations`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`agent_id` is the canonical agent key for state/commands/observations.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Optional auth token[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf `ROOMZERO_UNREAL_TOKEN` is unset, Unreal routes are public for local development.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf set, token is required for:[m
[32m+[m[32m- `POST /ws/unreal/command/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m[32m- `WS /ws/unreal/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAccepted token inputs:[m
[32m+[m[32m- query string: `?token=...`[m
[32m+[m[32m- header: `X-RoomZero-Unreal-Token: ...`[m
[32m+[m[32m- header: `Authorization: Bearer ...`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Protocol version[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCurrent expected value: `"roomzero.unreal.v1"`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll bridge model payloads include `protocol_version` and Unreal clients should verify it on every received message before processing.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Initial WebSocket state payload[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mImmediately after connect, backend sends current agent state:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "agent_id": "rz-01",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "emotion": "neutral",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "awareness": 0.5,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "trust": 0.2,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "is_speaking": false,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "is_observing": true,[m
[32m+[m[32m  "updated_at": "2025-01-01T12:00:00+00:00"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThen backend sends a greeting command payload (`type = "command"`).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Command message shape (backend -> Unreal)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommands are sent over WS and accepted via REST enqueue/broadcast path:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "command",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "agent_id": "rz-01",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "command": "speak",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "text": "I am RZ-01. I observe, learn, and reflect.",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "emotion": "curious",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "animation": "Gesture_Explain",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "duration_seconds": 4.0[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNotes:[m
[32m+[m[32m- `command` is required.[m
[32m+[m[32m- `text`, `emotion`, `animation`, `duration_seconds` are optional and command-specific.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Observation event shape (Unreal -> backend)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSend observations over WS with message `type = "observation"`:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "observation",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "event": "player_entered_room",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "payload": {[m
[32m+[m[32m    "distance": 2.4[m
[32m+[m[32m  }[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBackend stores observation with server timestamp and returns:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "ack",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "kind": "observation",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "agent_id": "rz-01",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "created_at": "2025-01-01T12:00:02+00:00"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf `event` is missing/empty, backend responds with:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "error",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "error": "missing_event"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Ping / pong behavior[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUnreal may send:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{ "type": "ping" }[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBackend responds:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "pong",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "agent_id": "rz-01"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Unknown/invalid message handling[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUnknown message type returns safe error payload:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m{[m
[32m+[m[32m  "type": "error",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "protocol_version": "roomzero.unreal.v1",[m
[32m+[m[32m  "error": "unknown_message_type"[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAdditional safety behaviors:[m
[32m+[m[32m- token failure on WS connect closes socket with code `1008`[m
[32m+[m[32m- command path/body `agent_id` mismatch returns HTTP 400[m
[32m+[m[32m- malformed observation payload defaults to `{}` for `payload` if non-object[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Unreal Integration Quick Guide[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mProtocol contract reference:[m
[32m+[m[32m- `docs/unreal_ws_contract.md` (schema-focused contract for `roomzero.unreal.v1`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Start backend (`.\run.ps1` or uvicorn).[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Unreal connects a WebSocket client to:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - `ws://127.0.0.1:8000/ws/unreal/{agent_id}`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - add token in query/header if enabled.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. On connect:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - read initial `AgentState`[m
[32m+[m[32m   - read greeting/queued `command` messages[m
[32m+[m[32m   - verify `protocol_version == "roomzero.unreal.v1"` before handling.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Send world observations as `type: "observation"` messages.[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Listen continuously for command messages and map them to animation/audio/behavior.[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Optionally send periodic `ping` and verify `pong`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBlueprint/C++ notes:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Keep a small dispatcher keyed by `type` (`command`, `ack`, `pong`, `error`, state payload).[m
[32m+[m[32m- Normalize numeric fields from JSON (`awareness`, `trust`, `duration_seconds`) with clamping.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Treat unknown fields as forward-compatible extensions; ignore safely.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Reconnect with backoff and re-read initial state after reconnect.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLocal testing:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Run automated test coverage:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - `python -m pytest -q RoomZero/tests/test_ws_unreal.py`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use smoke client:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - `python RoomZero/scripts/ws_unreal_smoke.py --agent-id rz-smoke`[m
[32m+[m[32m  - optional token via env:[m
[32m+[m[32m    - `set ROOMZERO_WS_TOKEN=your_token_here` (Windows cmd)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Inspect observations:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - `GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/ws/unreal/observations`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCI/local validation note:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Keep smoke execution local/controlled by running backend in the same job/session, then executing:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - `python RoomZero/scripts/ws_unreal_smoke.py --agent-id rz-smoke`[m
[32m+[m[32m- This avoids secret requirements when Unreal token auth is disabled for CI smoke scope.[m
[32m+[m[32m- If token auth is enabled in CI, provide token via ephemeral environment variable and never commit credentials.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Manual Unreal Integration Readiness Checklist[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBackend start command:[m
[32m+[m[32m- `python -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000`[m
[32m+[m
